.TH "hfi1_schedule_send_yield" 9 "hfi1_schedule_send_yield" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hfi1_schedule_send_yield \- test for a yield required for QP send engine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" hfi1_schedule_send_yield
.BI "(struct rvt_qp *qp "  ","
.BI "struct hfi1_pkt_state *ps "  ","
.BI "bool tid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "qp" 12
a pointer to QP
.IP "ps" 12
a pointer to a structure with commonly lookup values for
the the send engine progress
.IP "tid" 12
true if it is the tid leg
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine checks if the time slice for the QP has expired
for RC QPs, if so an additional work entry is queued. At this
point, other QPs have an opportunity to be scheduled. It
returns true if a yield is required, otherwise, false
is returned.
